      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not a typo. This is the way things are named in LLVM trunk (agreed that it is peculiar).\n\nWith respect to \"lib\" vs \"lib64\": passing the \"-flto\" option to clang causes it to add the following linker option:\n\n -plugin ${R}/../lib/LLVMgold.so\n\nwhere \"R\" is the bin directory that clang was derived from. So if LLVMgold.so is not in \"lib\", it won\u0027t be picked up correctly.",
      "parentUuid": "f9bdc694_3240311d",
      "revId": "142de256907367dfd0eb5fa4c75ac921351ffe1e",
